Today two years ago occurred the devastating atomic catastrophe of Fukushima, which after Chernobyl once again has left an entire region and with it the entire world looking down an atomic precipice. In the catastrophe in Japan a total of 16,000 people died, more than 2700 are still considered missing. Hundreds of thousands are living away from the irradiated homes. Today our thoughts are with the victims and their families. The Fukushima catastrophe has once again shown us just how uncontrollable and deadly the high risk atomic technology is. Therefore we have to make every conceivable effort in Germany, and also in Europe and worldwide, to bring about the transformation to renewable energy as rapidly as possible instead of pushing it off, as the CDU-FDP are trying to do again. Fukushima is warning us.â€
Claudia Roth is a highly influential politcian in Germany. She is not some uninformed twit off the street. In her comment she is communicating that it wasnâ€™t the tsunami that caused all the deaths in Japan â€“ ratherÂ it was the Fukushima accident, through manâ€™s negligence. This is as grotesqueÂ of aÂ revision of history and hideous lie as youâ€™ll ever find.
The fact is that not a single death has been attributed to the Fukushima accident to this day. Surely some will likely get ill and may die later on, but name one product that isnâ€™t capable of killing.
This tells us just how desperate the greens have gotten and the means theyâ€™ll resort to inÂ salvaging their green project of renewable energy. Now they have to shamelessly lie and fabricate an entirelyÂ new historical record that fits their agenda.
Can we believe them on climate science?
Now at Bild.
And at NTV.
