Antarctica has seen a whole bunch of harsh years recently, and it doesnâ€™t look like things are going to improve anytime soon.

Source: http://arctic.atmos.uiuc.edu/jpg.
Of course the extra sea ice weâ€™ve been seeing at the South Pole doesnâ€™t mean these dignified birdsÂ will become extinct any time soon. Like polar bears, theyâ€™ve survived far worse conditions. ButÂ it does mean the weaker ones arenâ€™t going to fare as well and some will have to make an agonizing, early departure from Earth.
Already Iâ€™mÂ seeing emperorÂ penguins falling from the sky to their death! Must be those damn man-made aerosols cooling the southern hemisphere.
